<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101022500215747></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101022500215747><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=101022500215747>RE: bonus points</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=101022500215747#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=133606><span id= >Kallirye</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>8 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Jan 5th 5:03 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think you have a good balance spread of points.  Personally, I think it is foolish for any character to dump all his points into one stat, on the other hand don't spread them out too thin either.<br><br>When I first created my character, everyone was saying, &quot;put it all in strength so you can carry stuff&quot;  I didn't listen to them and I'm glad now.  When I pictured the character I wanted to play for months or even years to come, I didn't imagine a buff and muscular female Dark Elf.  On the contrary I pictured a quick and agile fighter, maybe even a little lacking in the strength department.  I even considered, for a time, dumping most of my points in Charisma, which has little practical purpose in the game, but because I envisioned a beautiful warrior.  In the end I put most of my points in Agility, some in Dexterity and only 5 in Strength to round it out at 80.  Remember, Everquest is a 'roleplaying' game, your not trying to 'beat' anyone, there is no 'end' or big finale.  Even if you reach level 60 you can continue playing and still face many challenges or adventures.  Everyone told me not to pick a Dark Elf Shadow Knight as my first character, that it would be extremely difficult, especially for a newbie.  Guess what, 9 months later I'm only level 13, and it has been a little tough, though not as bad as I imagined, but I've had fun every step of the way, and wouldn't give up my Shadow Knight for a Million pp.  Remember, this is a game, have fun, and create the character you imagine in your head, and play it!<br>&nbsp;<br>Daughter of Hate, Shadow Knight of TheDead, Dedicated of Innoruuk, Consort of Emperor Crush.</td></tr>
